## Diagnosis

You're right — and this is a systemic documentation lag, not a one-off miss. The pattern is: **variant ships in component code → playground page is updated only after explicit feedback**. That's a broken feedback loop. The playground is treated as optional documentation rather than a mandatory delivery artifact.

**Anti-pattern: AP-072 — "Implementation Without Collocated Documentation"**
The component and its playground entry have no enforced coupling, so one can change without the other and CI stays green.

---

## Fix — Three Parts

### 1. Add `solid` to the Navigation Playground

**File: `src/app/(app)/playground/navigation/page.tsx`**

```tsx
import { Navigation } from "@/components/elan/Navigation";

const NAV_ITEMS = [
  { label: "Home",      href: "/" },
  { label: "Work",      href: "/work" },
  { label: "About",     href: "/about" },
  { label: "Contact",   href: "/contact" },
];

// ─── Exhaustive appearance list ───────────────────────────────────────────────
// ⚠️  KEEP IN SYNC WITH Navigation.tsx `appearance` prop union.
// When you add a variant there, add a section here. See CONTRIBUTING.md §Playground.
const APPEARANCES = ["default", "ghost", "solid"] as const;
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

export default function NavigationPlayground() {
  return (
    <main className="space-y-16 p-10">
      <h1 className="text-3xl font-semibold">Navigation — Playground</h1>

      {APPEARANCES.map((appearance) => (
        <section key={appearance} className="space-y-4">
          <h2 className="text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
            appearance=&quot;{appearance}&quot;
          </h2>

          {/* Default state */}
          <div className="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
            <Navigation items={NAV_ITEMS} appearance={appearance} />
          </div>

          {/* With active item */}
          <div className="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-6">
            <Navigation
              items={NAV_ITEMS}
              appearance={appearance}
              activeHref="/work"
            />
          </div>
        </section>
      ))}
    </main>
  );
}
```

---

### 2. Add a Lint-Time Safeguard — Exhaustiveness Check in the Component

This makes the compiler yell when `APPEARANCES` in the playground diverges from the prop union.

**File: `src/components/elan/Navigation.tsx`** (add near the type definitions)

```tsx
// ─── Appearance union ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export type NavigationAppearance = "default" | "ghost" | "solid";

// Exhaustiveness guard — the compiler will error here if the playground
// APPEARANCES array (imported as NavigationPlaygroundAppearances) ever
// diverges from this union. See CONTRIBUTING.md §Playground.
import type { NavigationPlaygroundAppearances } from
  "@/app/(app)/playground/navigation/appearances";

type _Guard = NavigationPlaygroundAppearances extends NavigationAppearance
  ? NavigationAppearance extends NavigationPlaygroundAppearances
    ? true
    : never  // ← compile error: playground is missing a variant
  : never;   // ← compile error: playground has an unknown variant
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

**File: `src/app/(app)/playground/navigation/appearances.ts`** *(new file)*

```ts
// Single source of truth consumed by both the playground page and the
// exhaustiveness guard in Navigation.tsx.
// Add every value that exists in NavigationAppearance here.
export const APPEARANCES = ["default", "ghost", "solid"] as const;
export type NavigationPlaygroundAppearances = (typeof APPEARANCES)[number];
```

Then update the playground page to import from this file:

```tsx
// src/app/(app)/playground/navigation/page.tsx
import { APPEARANCES } from "./appearances";
// (remove the inline const — it now lives in appearances.ts)
```

---

### 3. Codify the Rule — CONTRIBUTING.md

**File: `CONTRIBUTING.md`** (add or extend a `§ Playground` section)

```markdown
## § Playground — Mandatory Delivery Checklist

The playground is **not documentation sugar**. It is a required delivery
artifact with the same priority as the component itself.

### Rule PG-001 — Variant Parity (AP-072)

> Every value in a component's variant/appearance/size/state prop union
> **must** have a dedicated section in that component's playground page
> **before the PR is merged**.

#### How to comply

1. Open (or create) `src/app/(app)/playground/<component>/appearances.ts`.
2. Add your new variant value to the `APPEARANCES` const.
3. The exhaustiveness guard in the component file will produce a **compile
   error** until the playground file is updated — `pnpm build` (and the
   pre-push hook below) will catch it.
4. Confirm `pnpm playground:check` exits 0 (see Scripts below).

#### PR checklist item (add to pull_request_template.md)

- [ ] Playground updated for every new/changed variant (Rule PG-001)

### Scripts

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `pnpm playground:check` | Type-checks only playground pages + guard files |
| `pnpm build` | Full build; exhaustiveness guards run here too |

### Enforcement — pre-push hook

Install via `pnpm prepare` (Husky):

```sh
# .husky/pre-push
pnpm playground:check
```

```

**File: `package.json`** — add the check script

```json
"scripts": {
  "playground:check": "tsc --noEmit --project tsconfig.playground.json"
}
```

**File: `tsconfig.playground.json`** *(new)*

```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "include": [
    "src/app/(app)/playground/**/*",
    "src/components/elan/**/*"
  ]
}
```

---

## Principle

**Rule PG-001 (Anti-pattern AP-072 mitigation):** A variant and its playground entry are a single logical unit. They ship together or not at all. The exhaustiveness type guard converts a social convention ("remember to document it") into a compiler constraint ("the build fails until you do"). Documentation lag becomes impossible, not just discouraged.
